content: Today, we will study one short game.
Although the game itself was quite short, there is a lot to analyse about it.
First, let us begin with participation check, please press "i am here" button.

Xespok, slamduk, fallnavy, mayhem, scm2000, autickocz, CHaoshui, Before, Intotherenju, Andry, weigui, luwenzhe, SamSite, span, QBEN, 1m6z, endlessroad, Aurora, Renju_liu_t, virag, killer21st, coco_yuang, swordblue, yyfcsd, H8, LiuJianping.
Todays game shows the fight between two great masters.
they are both the champions of their country.
and they both have the 2nd place from WC, too.
which year did Yamaguchi get WC 2nd place and which year did Sinyov?
to be a good renju player, you should also know history.
poor memory, no good renju player :)
so, these two great players met again in 2003 WC.
And our today's game comes from there.
As already said, Sinyov was black here.
This 5th move is gaining popularity these years.
Some years ago, it was rarely used.
but now, it is perhaps even more frequently used than 5-i9.
Of course, there are some variations,
in my opinion, both have their advantages
white is required to defend differently,
because the lower side has 1 line short
of course white may have more choices for defense
but this example is good to show that with wider space black would win below
v 18-00 otkroi Olegu dver-ia na sobranii
it is a game style already
here, black cannot win, because of small space below
while, if 1 more line, black could win in this variant
So, my point is, both variants have their advantages
but also, in both cases there is some branch with edge problem
and white player should learn them well
With this 6th move, the variant can actually go to the same pattern:
but probably Igor Sinyov did not like those "popular" variants,
and wanted to try something different.
So he played the 7th move here.
Have you seen this 7th move before?
the traditional variant here goes something like this
what is the outcome of this variant in your opinion, good for black or white?
black is outside, should be good
let some new student show his idea then, QBEN

maybe black can use other ways?
eventually, the fight continues in upper side..
autickocz played well here, thanks! lets stop here.
the way he played shows quite well about the essence of this variant
in fact, most games of this variant go in similar manner
first white is active in lower corner,
then black spends some material to balance,
then white goes to upper side to defend,
Even today, it is hard for me to say who really has an advantage here.
probably with this 20 white can keep more open structures for self
anyway, this variant is very exciting,
but for some reason rarely played.
And for that reason Sinyov likely decided to try this 7th move.
Assuming that without good preparation Yamaguchi will not find a suitable plan for white here.
Yamaguchi was not prepared for this.
In fact, he already played the 8th move which is considered much weaker.
Of course, the natural move 9 followed.
It is a hard moment for white.
One would need to play aggressively now, to avoid being surrounded.
And by that, he put a serious task in front of Sinyov - to find win, or fail.
Because positional style is not so easily reached now.
You can now take a moment to think about black plan here, and we make a small participation check.
